        <div1 type="body">
            

<p><date when="1823-08-12">Augt. 12, 1823</date></p>
<p>Dr Sir,</p>

<p>I have engaged <persName>Mr Ingram</persName> as a <persName>Surveyor </persName>at the rate of five
dollars a mile he to find his <persName>chain carriers</persName> and marker You will
please direct him as to the quantity to be surveyed in each tract and
the manner of laying it off&#8212;As a genl rule no Sitio tracts ought
to be divided but I agreed to divide <persName>Mr Castleman</persName>s, as otherwise
he cannot get his quantity without interfering with <persName>Rabb </persName>or 
<persName>Buckner</persName>&#8212;I shall return by the time you have finished those two surveys,
and will meet you at <persName>Woods</persName>&#8212;</p>

<p><persName>Stephen F. Austin</persName>    [Rubric]</p>

<p>El <persName>Baron De Bastrop</persName></p>

        </div1>
